Going back to Hallworth’s comment, it seems appropriate that health care for inmates is at least adequate, as neglect of medical care is in clear violation of the Eighth Amendment. Court rulings referenced by Meyer and Weaver (2006; e.g., 
Knecht v. Gilman, 1973; 
Washington v. Harper, 1990) show an awareness of mental health in prisons, further expanding the concept of satisfactory health care in prisons to include mental health.
